org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine.invoke
Class AeProcessInvokeHandler

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine.invoke.AeProcessInvokeHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeInvokeHandler, IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback, IAeTwoPhaseInvokeHandler
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeSubprocessInvokeHandler
public class AeProcessInvokeHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements IAeTwoPhaseInvokeHandler, IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback

Handler created by the AeProcessHandlerFactory. This handler is responsible for invokes based on the 'process' custom invoke protocol.

handleInvoke

public IAeWebServiceResponse handleInvoke(IAeInvoke aInvoke,
                                          java.lang.String aQueryData)
Invokes the given process. The process to invoke for this handler is specified as a QName in the wsa::Address field of the endpoint reference. If the QName is not specified or if the deployment plan for the given QName is not found, this handler will generate a system fault.

Specified by:
handleInvoke in interface IAeInvokeHandler
Parameters:

onNotAcknowledge

public void onNotAcknowledge(java.lang.Throwable aReason)
Description copied from interface: IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback
Called if the message cannot be delivered. A typical use case if a one-way correlated message was queued to the engine and the engine did not find matching message receiver with in a predetermined time.

Specified by:
onNotAcknowledge in interface IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback
Parameters:
aReason - Optional exception that was the root cause of non-delivery. This parameter may be null.

createReplyReceiver

protected IAeReplyReceiver createReplyReceiver(IAeInvokeInternal aInvoke,
                                               IAeMessageContext aWsioMsgContext)
                                        throws AeException
Creates and returns the reply receiver. This implementation returns a AeDurableQueuingReplyReceiver if the invoke is a two way invoke. The current AeInvokeResponse is flagged as early reply (async). Returns null for one-way invokes.
